Explanation:

The solution uses a simple approach to count the number of opening and closing parentheses in the given string. It iterates through the string and updates the count of opening and closing parentheses accordingly. If the count of closing parentheses becomes greater than the count of opening parentheses, it means that there are unmatched opening parentheses. In this case, it subtracts the count of closing parentheses from the count of opening parentheses. Finally, it returns the count of opening parentheses. This solution has a high efficiency as it only iterates through the string once, resulting in a time complexity of O(n). The space complexity is O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space to store the counts.

